\left\{\dfrac{nx}{2+n+x}\right\}^{\infty}_{1}
f(x) = x
x \in [0, 1]
\begin{align}\left|\dfrac{nx}{2+n+x}-x\right| &= \left|\dfrac{nx-x(2+n+x)}{2+n+x}\right| \\ &= \left|\dfrac{-2x-x^{2}}{2+n+x}\right| \\ &= \left|\dfrac{2x+x^{2}}{2+n+x}\right| \\ &\leq \left|\dfrac{2x+x^{2}}{2+n}\right| \text{ since } x \in [0, 1] \\ &\leq \left|\dfrac{3}{2+n}\right| \text{ since } x \in [0, 1] \\ &< \left|\dfrac{3}{n}\right| \\ &= \dfrac{3}{n} \\ &< \dfrac{3}{\left(\dfrac{1}{3\epsilon}\right)} = \epsilon\end{align}
